NUMBER 3454
NAME Narrow Boulders
DEEPCAVE
*DESCRIPTION_START
Once beyond the opening, you enter a what appears to be a small chimney-type niche in the face of the cliff itself. To either side of the you walls recede just far enough that you cannot make contact with both at the same time. A pair of massive boulders have firmly blocked any passage deeper into the cliff and to the east, it opens back onto the main valley.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 78
EXTEND 0 wedged into the base of the niche
ITEM 1 78
EXTEND 1 wedged securely on top of the first
ITEM 2 420 ADJ1=401
ITEM 3 420 ADJ2=402
EXIT E 721
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
This boulder is huge and firmly wedged into the base of the niche.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
This boulder is nearly as huge as the first, and somehow managed to get wedged into place on top of it.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFTOUCH 2
 IFVAR FLAG4 = 2
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You cannot reach %a while touching the other wall!
  ECHO OTHERS %n tries to touch both walls at the same time, and cannot.
 ELSE
  EQUAL FLAG4 1
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFTOUCH 3
 IFVAR FLAG4 = 1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You cannot reach %a while touching the other wall!
  ECHO OTHERS %n tries to touch both walls at the same time, and cannot.
 ELSE
  EQUAL FLAG4 2
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB SNIFF -1
 IFVAR WOLFFORM ! 1
  ECHO PLAYER You smell nothing in particular.
 ELSE
  ECHO PLAYER You scent the faint smell of wolves leading up to the boulders.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB CLIMB 0
 IFVAR FLAG3 ! 1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You cannot find a suitable place to climb the boulder.
 ELSE
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You clamber easily up the boulder, and drop through the opening between them to the other side.
  ECHO OTHERS %n scrambles up the lowest boulder and vanishes.
  MOVEGROUP 3455
  AFFECT 3455
  ECHO OTHERS %n scrambles through the opening in the boulders towards you.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB CLIMB 1
 CLEARVERB
 ECHO PLAYER That boulder is far too high for you to climb.
 ECHO OTHERS %n looks way up at the higher boulder.
ENDIF
IFVERB SEARCH -1
 RANDOM DUMMY1 1 10 0
 IFVAR DUMMY1 > 6
  ECHO PLAYER Walking around the side of the boulders you notice a small opening where one has evidently fallen atop the other.
  ECHO PLAYER You realize that you will have to climb the lowermost boulder to get to the opening.
  EQUAL FLAG3 1
 ELSE
  ECHO PLAYER Your search recovers nothing extraordinary.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
