NUMBER 3455
NAME Within the Narrow Chasm
DEEPCAVE
*DESCRIPTION_START
The high walls of this chasm stretch loomingly above you into the sky. At their crest, the cliff faces grow so closely together that they form only a small fissure in the floor of the mountain above. Enough light to see filters in but little more than that is available. To the east, the opening back through the boulders looks easily accessible.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 1 72 VAL2=3454
EXIT N 3456
IFVERB SNIFF -1
 IFVAR WOLFFORM ! 1
  ECHO PLAYER You smell nothing in particular.
 ELSE
  ECHO PLAYER You smell a wolf scent, but it is old and mingles with the smell of dust in the air.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 3456
NAME Within the Narrow Chasm
DEEPCAVE
*DESCRIPTION_START
You stand within a narrow defile, which is open to the sky far above you, yet at its widest portion is well under three feet across. To the north you can see a hint of brighter light where the canyon opens upon a small circular cul-de-sac, deep within the cliffside. To the northeast the walls seem to meet overhead, coloring the canyon with dark shadows.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT N 3457
EXIT NE 3458
EXIT S 3455
IFVERB SNIFF -1
 IFVAR WOLFFORM ! 1
  ECHO PLAYER You smell nothing in particular.
 ELSE
  ECHO PLAYER To the north you scent an inviting liquid aroma, while the faint scent of wolves wafts from the northeast.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 3457
NAME Within the Narrow Chasm
DEEPCAVE
*DESCRIPTION_START
A circular shaft descends down from above, creating a small hollow within this strange rocky landscape. Down the sides of the shaft, water sheets in glistening waves, finally collecting in a pool which lays in front of you. A great slab of rock extends out from the circular walls forming a ledge, directly over the surface of the pool a scant foot and a half above its surface.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 324 ADJ2=442
extend 0 which has collected in the darkness under a slab of rock
ITEM 1 1599
ITEM 2 420 ADJ1=944 ADJ2=346
extend 1 of rock extending out from the walls
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
Peering under the slab of rock, you see a pool of water, collecting from the glistening liquid which sheets down the smooth walls of the hollow. For some unknown reason the water seems to pulse regularly with a faint glow.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
This large, flat rock extends horizontally from the glistening wall of the cul-de-sac, forming a low shelf over the pool.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
The wall glistens with a brilliant rainbow colored sheen reflected from the thin layer of moisture that sheets continuously down its face.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFTOUCH 2
 CLEARVERB
 ECHO PLAYER You reach out and touch %a.
 ECHO OTHERS %n reaches out and touches %a.
 PLREVENT 0
 CONTPLREVENT
 ECHO PLAYER You only feel the slightest bit of moisture from the incredibly thin sheet of water.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GO 1
 IFVAR FLAG4 = 0
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You scramble up onto the slab of rock.
  ECHO OTHERS %n scrambles up onto the slab of rock.
  EQUAL FLAG4 1
 ELSE
  ECHO PLAYER You walk around the top of the slab.
  ECHO OTHERS %n walks around the top of the slab.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB JUMP -1
 IFVAR FLAG4 = 1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You jump off the low slab.
  ECHO OTHERS %n jumps off the low slab.
  EQUAL FLAG4 0
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB SOUTH -1
 IFVAR FLAG4 = 1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You cannot leave without first jumping off the slab.
  ECHO OTHERS %n looks at the opening to the south from the top of the slab.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFTOUCH 0
 IFVAR FLAG4 ! 1
  IFVAR WOLFFORM ! 1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You cannot fit under the slab, and cannot reach the pool.
   ECHO OTHERS %n tries to squeeze %iself under the slab, but cannot.
  ELSE
   ECHO PLAYER You inch your way under the slab.
   ECHO OTHERS %n inches his way under the slab.
  ENDIF
 ELSE
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You cannot reach the pool through the slab you stand upon.
  ECHO OTHERS %n looks down at the surface of the slab.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB DRINK 0
 CLEARVERB
 IFVAR ROUNDTIME < 1
  IFVAR FLAG4 ! 1
   IFVAR WOLFFORM ! 1
    ECHO PLAYER You cannot fit under the slab, and cannot reach the pool.
    ECHO OTHERS %n tries to squeeze %iself under the slab, but cannot.
   ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER You dip your snout into the water and drink deeply.
    ECHO OTHERS %n dips %h snout into the water and drinks deeply.
    EQUAL ROUNDTIME 1
    SPELL 537 99
    ECHO PLAYER [Round: 1 sec]
   ENDIF
  ELSE
   ECHO PLAYER You cannot reach the pool through the slab you stand upon.
   ECHO OTHERS %n looks down at the surface of the slab.
  ENDIF
 ELSE
  STRCVT 0 ROUNDTIME
  ECHO PLAYER Please wait %0 seconds...
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB LOOK 0
 IFVAR FLAG4 = 1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You cannot see the pool through the slab you stand upon.
  ECHO OTHERS %n stares down at the surface of the slab.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
EXIT S 3456
;
NUMBER 3458
NAME A Large Chamber
DEEPCAVE
*DESCRIPTION_START
The defile opens up into a large chamber with many small offshoots and alcoves. This place seems a nearly perfect environment for animals to live or sleep and judging from the scattered bones and claw marks upon the walls, you are not the only one to realize this. All signs of habitation, however, are extremely old. It seems that nothing has lived here for a very long time.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT SW 3456
ITEM 0 63 VAL2=3459
IFPREVERB GO 0
 IFVAR FLAG3 ! 1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER What are you referring to?
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFTOUCH 0
 IFVAR FLAG3 ! 1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER What are you referring to?
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB SMELL -1
 IFVAR WOLFFORM = 1
  ECHO PLAYER You catch the strong scent of another wolf coming from somewhere nearby.
  EQUAL FLAG3 47
 ELSE
  ECHO PLAYER You take a deep breath.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB SEARCH -1
 IFVAR FLAG3 = 47
  PLREVENT 1
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO PLAYER You find a narrow crevice, hidden in the natural folds of the east wall.
  EQUAL FLAG3 1
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFENTRY
 IFVAR WOLFSHOW = 1
  EQUAL WOLFSHOW 0
  PLREVENT 1
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL Out of the corner of your eye you see a large shape dart out of an alcove followed by many more.
  PLREVENT 1
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL As you turn to look you notice that all you spy are shadows, playing upon the walls of the cavern.
  PLREVENT 1
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL The shadows take on the distinct outlines of wolves and other strange haunched beasts locked in a terrible battle of fury.
  PLREVENT 1
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL As the battle continues, humanoid shadows emerge from every corner, transforming as they leap into the fray.
  PLREVENT 1
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL The wolf images of the cavern, however, are soon overwhelmed as more and more of the strange haunched beasts pour in through the entrance.
  PLREVENT 1
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL For a long moment you forget that you are simply watching silhouettes flickering on the cavern wall, carried away by the lingering savagery.
  PLREVENT 1
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL Soon, all of the wolf shadows have fallen and fade into the darkness of the cavern floor.
  PLREVENT 3
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL A great wailing mournful howl rises from the caverns about you, tearing at your heart with its hopeless beauty.
  AFFECT 3454
  ECHO ALL A great wailing mournful howl rises from the cliffs about you, tearing at your heart with its hopeless beauty.
  AFFECT 3455
  ECHO ALL A great wailing mournful howl rises from the cliffs about you, tearing at your heart with its hopeless beauty.
  AFFECT 3456
  ECHO ALL A great wailing mournful howl rises from the cliffs about you, tearing at your heart with its hopeless beauty.
  AFFECT 3457
  ECHO ALL A great wailing mournful howl rises from the cliffs about you, tearing at your heart with its hopeless beauty.
  AFFECT 3459
  ECHO ALL A great wailing mournful howl rises from the caverns about you, tearing at your heart with its hopeless beauty.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB HOWL -1
 IFVAR WOLFFORM = 1
  PLREVENT 1
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL The howl echoes through the cavern, strangely magnified, as if scores of wolves were answering in chorus.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
