NUMBER 3459
NAME Small Cavern
DEEPCAVE
*DESCRIPTION_START
You stand within a small cavern off the main complex of chambers. A pile of ancient furs lays in one corner. Sketched on the walls in some dark substance which has withstood the test of time are simple images of everyday life long ago. The unfinished floor has been packed so hard by the passage of countless feet that no dust is disturbed by your passage. A crevice leads back out to the main chamber.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 1040
EXTEND 0 of ancient furs
ITEM 2 63 VAL2=3458
ITEM 3 420
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The furs radiate a sense of great age, yet were so well treated and cared for that they still look warm and inviting.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 3
Upon the wall you see paintings depicting wolves sitting about on a circle of boulders, hunting large herds of creatures with huge racks of antlers, running along-side two-legged human figures, and fighting other wolves drawn with black coats and red shining eyes.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFENTRY
 IFVAR PLRSINROOM = 1
  EQUAL WOLFGHOST 0
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB SMELL -1
 IFVAR WOLFFORM = 1
  PLREVENT 0
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO PLAYER You smell a strong wolf-scent on the pile of old furs.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFTOUCH 0
 IFVAR WOLFGHOST = 0
  IFVAR RAC = 4
   EQUAL WOLFGHOST 1
   PLREVENT 2
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO ALL The pile of furs rustles as if something within were alive.
   PLREVENT 2
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO ALL The furs stop rustling as an ethereal figure rises from within them.
   PLREVENT 1
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO ALL The figure solidifies into a ghostly wolfling man, who looks at you curiously.
   EQUAL WOLFGHOST 2
   NEWITEM 1 1587 ADJ1=1374 ADJ2=353
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFSAY HELLO
 IFVAR WOLFGHOST = 2
  PLREVENT 0
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL The ghostly wolfling says, "Greetings, and welcome to an old wolfling's home."
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFSAY GREETINGS
 IFVAR WOLFGHOST = 2
  PLREVENT 0
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL The ghostly wolfling says, "Greetings, and welcome to an old wolfling's home."
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFSAY WOLFLING?
 IFVAR WOLFGHOST = 2
  PLREVENT 0
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL The ghostly wolfling says, "Yes, I am a wolfling"
  PLREVENT 0
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL Without warning, the ghostly wolfling howls and collapses to the ground, shaking.
 ECHO ALL Undergoing a terrible transformation, he changes shape into that of a wolf!
 PLREVENT 3
 CONTPLREVENT
 ECHO ALL A wolf suddenly howls, writhing in pain. It transforms into a ghostly wolfling.
  PLREVENT 2
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL The ghostly wolfling bares his fangs.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFSAY HOME?
 IFVAR WOLFGHOST = 2
  PLREVENT 0
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL The ghostly wolfling says, "Yes, this den is our home. Certainly you ran into my packmates on your way in?"
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFSAY DEN?
 IFVAR WOLFGHOST = 2
  PLREVENT 0
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL The ghostly wolfling says, "This cavernous haven is our den, the largest in the land."
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFSAY PACKMATES?
 IFVAR WOLFGHOST = 2
  PLREVENT 0
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL The ghostly wolfling says, "Yes, my pack lives here, you must have seen them outside? Ah, no matter. I teach the younger ones how to fight and survive in the world."
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFSAY PACK?
 IFVAR WOLFGHOST = 2
  PLREVENT 0
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL The ghostly wolfling says, "My Pack? We live here in the mountains, fighting fiercely for the She-Wolf, and her land."
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFSAY FIGHT?
 IFVAR WOLFGHOST = 2
  PLREVENT 0
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL The ghostly wolfling says, "Yes, we fight with tooth and claw, as a wolfling should. I used to train all of our warriors so that they may face the cursed ones with pride."
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFSAY MOTHER?
 IFVAR WOLFGHOST = 2
  PLREVENT 0
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL The ghostly wolfling says, "The She-Wolf, our mother, the one who created this land and all within it. Then, when danger threatened, she lay with the human, Aimanear,  to beget the first wolflings."
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFSAY SHE-WOLF?
 IFVAR WOLFGHOST = 2
  PLREVENT 0
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL The ghostly wolfling says, "The She-Wolf, our mother, the one who created this land and all within it. Then, when danger threatened, she lay with the human, Aimanear,  to beget the first wolflings."
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFSAY AIMANEAR?
 IFVAR WOLFGHOST = 2
  PLREVENT 0
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL The ghostly wolfling says, "Our first Sire. Legend has it that he was a mighty two-leg warrior, who was favored of the She-Wolf, our Mother."
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFSAY LAND?
 IFVAR WOLFGHOST = 2
  PLREVENT 0
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL The ghostly wolfling says, "The Land? Why, the Land is our sacred trust, given to us by our mother to protect from the forces that would despoil it."
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFSAY FORCES?
 IFVAR WOLFGHOST = 2
  PLREVENT 0
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL The ghostly wolfling says, "The tainted ones, created cursed, whose aim is to twist the very fabric of our mother's creation to their foul ends!"
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFSAY TAINTED?
 IFVAR WOLFGHOST = 2
  PLREVENT 0
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL The ghostly wolfling says, "Yes, the taint of weredom, created by their foul god."
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFSAY CURSED?
 IFVAR WOLFGHOST = 2
  PLREVENT 0
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL The ghostly wolfling says, "Cursed by the touch of the foul Shaltos, who desires only the end of our mother's creation!"
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFSAY god?
 IFVAR WOLFGHOST = 2
  PLREVENT 0
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL The ghostly wolfling says, "Yes, Shaltos, an eternal bane on our mother's existance."
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFSAY SHALTOS?
 IFVAR WOLFGHOST = 2
  PLREVENT 0
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL The ghostly wolfling says, "Yes, an evil god, who created the parodies of ourselves that most call werewolves."
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFSAY SHALTOS_IS_DEAD
 IFVAR WOLFGHOST = 2
  PLREVENT 0
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL The ghostly wolfling says, "That cannot be. You must be mistaken, for how can one kill a god?"
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFSAY SHALTOS_IS_DEAD!
 IFVAR WOLFGHOST = 2
  PLREVENT 0
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL The ghostly wolfling says, "Dead you say? I cannot believe that, I have seen the evidence of his cursed work. That is not the hand of a dead god!"
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFSAY TRAIN?
 IFVAR WOLFGHOST = 2
  PLREVENT 0
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL The ghostly wolfling says, "No, I am no longer agile enough to teach."
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFSAY WEREWOLF?
 IFVAR WOLFGHOST = 2
  PLREVENT 0
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL The ghostly wolfling spits on the floor, and says, "Do not mention those foul creatures here."
  PLREVENT 2
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL The ghostly wolfling continues, "In truth, I fear we are expecting an attack here at any time.
  EQUAL FLAG4 1
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFSAY WEREDOM?
 IFVAR WOLFGHOST = 2
  PLREVENT 0
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL The ghostly wolfling says, "Yes, werewolves, the cursed ones."
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFSAY WEREWOLVES?
 IFVAR WOLFGHOST = 2
  PLREVENT 0
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL The ghostly wolfling spits on the floor, and says, "Do not mention those foul creatures here."
  PLREVENT 2
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL The ghostly wolfling continues, "In truth, I fear we are expecting an attack here at any time.
  EQUAL FLAG4 1
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFSAY ATTACK?
 IFVAR WOLFGHOST = 2
  IFVAR FLAG4 ! 1
   ECHO ALL The ghostly wolfling seems confused by the question.
  ELSE
   PLREVENT 0
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO ALL The ghostly wolfling says, "Yes, a small group of the Cursed Ones discovered this lair a few nights ago."
   PLREVENT 1
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO ALL The ghostly wolfling continues, "We attacked savagely when they entered, but I am afraid that two of the creatures escaped."
   PLREVENT 1
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO ALL The ghostly wolfling finishes, "Tonight the moons are full, so we expect an attack in force at any moment. I should be seeing to the defenses now."
   PLREVENT 0
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO ALL The ghostly figure seems to flicker and fade as it leaves for the outer chamber.
   ECHO ALL Almost immediately you hear a howl of challenge from the main cavern.
   EQUAL WOLFGHOST 0
   EQUAL WOLFSHOW 1
   REMOVEITEM 1
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB LISTEN -1
 PLREVENT 0
 CONTPLREVENT
 ECHO PLAYER You hear a faint deep throaty sound as if several wolves were quietly growling to one another nearby.
ENDIF
